Fix: Wait for Reveal.js to load with polling

This patch fixes the Reveal.js initialization by using a polling mechanism instead of window.load event.

Apply this change to: packages/cluster-quest/public/app.js

Around line 869-874, replace:

```javascript
// Attendre que Reveal.js soit chargé
if (typeof Reveal !== 'undefined') {
    initializeRevealJS();
} else {
    window.addEventListener('load', initializeRevealJS);
}
```

With:

```javascript
// Attendre que Reveal.js soit chargé
function waitForReveal() {
    if (typeof Reveal !== 'undefined') {
        console.log('✅ Reveal.js détecté, initialisation...');
        initializeRevealJS();
    } else {
        console.log('⏳ Attente de Reveal.js...');
        setTimeout(waitForReveal, 100);
    }
}

// Démarrer l'attente
waitForReveal();
```

This ensures Reveal.js is properly detected and initialized even in iframe contexts where load events may not fire reliably.
